Energy (ARPA-E) During our tenure at , we partnered to build a software platform that harnessed the power of machine learning to track and improve the impact of research At the time, Ann was also directing an R&D program that uses integrated transportation and energy models to identify emission reduction strategies from the transportation Two things became apparent through that experience: the only meaningful strategy to decarbonize the transportation sector is through electrification advanced simulation tools can break down the information barrier to vehicle electrification that stands between the transportation and electric power sectors So Ann went back to R&D at the Texas A&M Transportation Institute, where she created a uniquely scalable toolkit that could utilize transportation data to predict future electric vehicle (EV) demand and project its impact on utility grids, city infrastructure, and overall She reached back out to Patrick to spin out a new company dedicated solely to ensuring that the transition to electric transport be as quick and efficient as Thus, ElectroTempo was We are now striving to change the world by bringing advanced analytics to bear in identifying where and how much EV charging and grid infrastructure is needed to empower an electric Our story ElectroTempo was founded as a collaboration between transportation specialist Ann Xu and energy technology commercialization specialist Patrick Our shared passion of making the world a better, more sustainable place by reducing emissions brought us together at the Department of Energy s Advanced Research Projects Agency - Privacy Policy Last Updated on January , Your privacy is important to This Privacy Policy (this "Policy") applies to services provided by , ("we," "us," "our" or "1v1Me"), as well as our affiliates and subsidiaries, and to our website (the "Site"), mobile app and or other platform(s) (collectively, the "Services") and explains what information we collect from users or visitors of our Services (each, a "user," "you" or "your"), including information that may be used to personally identify you ("Personal Information"), and how we use We encourage you to read the details This Policy applies to any user of our We will be the controller of your personal data provided to, collected by or for or processed in connection with our We reserve the right to change this Policy at any We will notify you of material changes to this Policy by sending notice to the primary email address specified in your account or by a prominent notice on our Changes and clarifications will take effect You should periodically check our website, including the page on which this Policy is located, for You acknowledge that your continued use of our Services after we publish or send a notice about our changes to this Policy means that the collection, use and or sharing of your Personal Information is subject to the updated What Information Do We Collect? Information Provided by You We collect information that you knowingly give us when you create an account, contact us or otherwise access or use our This may include: Your full name, email address, residential address, citizenship, telephone number, social security number, date of birth, employment information (including status and employer information, if applicable), responses to surveys that we may ask you to complete for research purposes or to help direct activities and social media account information The contact information of your representative, if any and or Details of any financial transactions you participate in on the Services, including the amount, currency and method of Information Collected Automatically We automatically or passively collect information when you access or use our This may include: Device type used to access our website (i.e., computer or mobile device), unique number assigned to identify such device, your device s operating system, your device s application version and your device s internet protocol (IP) address Whenever you visit or interact with our website, information about how our website is accessed and used, including, but not limited to, click path taken through our website, your use of features or applications on our website and or other publicly available information this data is generally , but, if we associate it with you as an identifiable person, we will treat it as Personal Information and or If you access our Services from a mobile device, your device s unique mobile platform advertising identifier, such as Apple s "Identifier for Advertising ID" or Google s "Android Advertising ID" ("mobile advertising identifiers"), and the ways you use the â How Do We Use the Information We Collect? We use the information we collect to: Deliver and improve the Services and your overall user experience Protect against, investigate and deter fraudulent, unauthorized and or illegal activity Link or combine user information with other Personal Information Compare and verify information for accuracy and update our records Validate information for identity verification, including verification for laundering and "Know Your Customer" protocols Email, message or otherwise contact you with information and updates about us and the Services, and respond to your comments and questions if you ve provided us with the means to do so On a , aggregated basis, analyze how you use the Services with tools like Google Analytics to help us understand traffic patterns and know if there are problems with the Services and or Create targeted advertising to promote the Services and engage our  Do We Share Your Personal Information? We do not rent, sell or share your Personal Information with third parties except with your consent or as necessary to complete any transaction or provide any service you have requested or authorized in this In connection with the Services, we may provide your Personal Information to the following third parties: Partners: Sometimes we collaborate with others to deliver the Services, and may provide such Personal Information as required by our partners who do not have an independent use of the information we disclose to Affiliates: We may share your information with our affiliates and or Service providers: We work with a wide range of service providers, notably our database administrators, cloud computing services, advertising services, data analysts, application service providers, identity verification services and other organizations, and may provide such information as required by any such service provider in connection with the performance of the appli

WunderGraph Skip to main content Menu WunderGraph Docs Principles Blog Talk to us Discord 🌜 🌞 WunderGraph Docs Principles Blog Talk to us Discord Secure by default # Any tool would make or at least try to make this claim, right? So how does WunderGraph make a difference in terms of security? How GraphQL Servers work # To get a better understanding of why WunderGraph is "secure by default" we need to first have a look at the steps involved of executing a GraphQL Query from the perspective of a GraphQL Server: accepts the request reads the request body parse the request JSON extract the Query from the JSON lexing parsing normalization validation execution build the JSON response send response to client Of those steps lexing, parsing and validating a Query are highly vulnerable to attacks of any sort that try to inject unexpected If an attacker get s around validation in some way they re able to execute what was previously known as SQL Because of the dynamic character of GraphQL every GraphQL implementation and framework is vulnerable to this Nowadays there are numerous implementations of the GraphQL specification in any possible Can you trust the implementation or framework you use? # As of today there is no standard to validate the correct implementation of the GraphQL specification under all possible The community would really benefit from such a tool by which implementations could for example be All you can do is use extensive testing, fuzzing to make sure the implementation is as correct as But is it really your business to make sure an implementation is correct? Is there a simpler way to get the benefits of GraphQL without making your systems vulnerable? Don t expose GraphQL at all # With WunderGraph you have to persist all Queries by There s no way around Queries get defined and persisted by a developer in the WunderGraph Clients cannot register their own Queries at This reduces the additional attack surface of GraphQL to To the API consumer it looks like any other REST or RPC All the steps like lexing, parsing, validation, happen when the developer saves a new Queries get then automatically prepared on your At runtime all that happens is the execution of the prepared Summary # All implementations and frameworks are easy to attack as long as don t have a standardized way of guaranteeing If you use WunderGraph this attack vector can be eliminated because your server never get s directly exposed to the Try us out! The basics # When you first learned about GraphQL one of the first concepts you had to understand is that GraphQL sends Queries via POST Because of this it s not possible to cache these Caching is only possible on GET The last paragraph is not really To be more precise, it s not possible for Browsers and intermediate caches like CDNs to cache POST Persisted Queries # Some of you might have already heard of persisted To get everyone on the same page: Persisted Queries are a very simple You take a Query, store it on a server and give it a Now you create a GET endpoint that accepts variables as Query The Query is now persisted and can be cached easily by HTTP Here s an example: query AllOpenTasks tasks ( done : false ) id title Copy If you persist this AllOpenTasks Query your endpoint might look like this: http : example . com api AllOpenTasks ? variables = "done" : "false" Copy Considerations if you want to roll your own # You have to write and maintain the code You need to deploy and operate another service Will you redeploy the service if the persisted Queries change? Keep in mind that you cannot always upgrade all clients at once You need to figure out the exact headers to set Do you want to support caching for private (authenticated) APIs too? In that case you also have to validate the user s identity Do you want the Cache server to also keep responses in a cache? If so, will you deploy the service multiple times for high availability and performance reasons? If so, you also have to find a solution for a shared Let WunderGraph take care of it # Solving all the above problems might not be your core

florrent florrent Get More Info Get More Info About Us florrent is a , ClimateTech company innovating to design and build the next generation of high energy density ultracapacitors that will stabilize electrical grids and address critical bottlenecks for the adoption of renewable energies, electric vehicles, and buildings . Our ultracapacitors are manufactured in Western Massachusetts from abundant and regenerative hemp biomass , grown domestically in the US by Black and Indigenous farmers . Mission & Vision florrent will be a cornerstone of the just energy transition to a resilient, renewable, and equitable energy Our products enable a constellation of energy sovereign communities to generate, store, and use renewable power Gigawatts of our ultracapacitors will be deployed across the world, sequestering gigatons of carbon into the Values & Impact At florrent, we are not just striving to unlock a world powered by clean We believe that how we get there and who we bring along on the journey are just as important, and that diverse teams generate more innovative solutions to the world’s greatest At every possible stage of our value chain, florrent will be a contributor in restoring humanization and to historically oppressed peoples and The Challenge We re Solving Renewables & batteries alone cannot support our electrifying world Today’s electrical grid was not designed to balance variable and intermittent energy production from distributed renewable sources like wind and solar against the increasingly dynamic power demands of ubiquitous EV charging and Renewables + HYBRID STORAGE = Electrification As renewables and electrification rapidly expand, high power transients will overburden conventional battery systems deployed on the Batteries are like marathon runners that do well running hours over flat ground at steady state, but struggle to sprint the florrent’s ultracapacitors are the sprinters that will keep battery systems operating longer and Pairing ultracapacitors with conventional grid batteries to handle the expensive grid demands of the future will improve grid profitability and reliability, putting the focus back where we need it: on the decarbonizing technologies of the future Learn More About Investing, Deploying Our Ultracapacitors, or Joining the Team florrent is scaling rapidly to unlock a world powered by clean energy and increase the stability and resiliency of the world’s electrical Please contact us if Introducing Rewire — Rewire Home Home 1 September Nick Nettleton Introducing Rewire Nick Nettleton 1 September Introducing Rewire Nick Nettleton 1 September Hello — I’m Nick Nettleton, founder of the web engineering agency Loft Digital and its parent, the Loft Group . Today I am introducing Rewire , the newest member of our Its purpose is to help clients build breakthrough artificial intelligence technology into their businesses and With ten years’ experience building web apps, systems and platforms, we are perfectly positioned to provide this specialist By way of a little background, it’s fifteen years since I set up in business, twenty years since I created my first website — and thirty years since I first learned how to programme a I remember the occasion I was ten, it was Christmas, and we were at my grandfather’s My present was a futuristic little white android with wheels, a clock, a lot of buttons, a tape recorder, and bona fide magic under the It was an Omnibot , and it was the coolest and most exciting thing I ever I “taught” my robot, by recording a sequence movements, to pick up a snack in the kitchen and bring it to me in the This kind of worked, but it had a tendency to go off piste at the slightest challenge — a bit of buckled carpet, or a slippery wooden floor, for example — and then it could never correct So the semblance of intelligence was really very No It was enough to inspire me with a lifelong passion for the extraordinary potential of computing to change the “The most important technology anybody on the planet is working on today” Until very recently, robots and artificial intelligence were not really at the forefront of tech When I founded Loft Digital in , web apps and social networks were the big Then it was mobile, then the cloud, then big data, and most recently Over the years the Loft team have helped many others achieve extraordinary things through these We have been part of a movement which, in less than a decade, has transformed our world and the lives of billions of people for the Now AI is back on the agenda, very suddenly, and in a very big way Massive investment from the likes of Google, Apple, IBM, Tesla, Amazon, Microsoft and others, combined with unprecedented computational power, data, research and programming , have enabled critical technologies in the AI stack to mature and come together at Now they are ready to be used in Not just FTSE , but all types and sizes of organisation, in every single I am talking here about a massive new wave of commercial disruption, world betterment, economic growth and technology If that sounds like hyperbole, consider what Dave Coplin, Microsoft’s Chief Envisioning Officer, recently said : “AI is the most important technology that anybody on the planet is working on today … This technology will change how we relate to It will change how we relate to each I would argue that it will even change how we perceive what it means to be ” By , everything will be Some say AI will be a $70bn industry . Its impact will be far In a world changing this fast, we know our clients and potential clients are going to need That’s why we at Loft have set up Rewire: a brand new kind of agency, consultancy, programming outfit — whatever it needs to be — to help clients get the latest breakthrough AI technology working in their In this way, it is our clients who will offer the best products and services on the market, who will do the disrupting, and who will operate in the most efficient For those with opportunities to integrate AI into their digital infrastructure and web properties, we’ll have the core Loft Digital and Rewire teams working together around the Over the coming months I’ll be sharing ideas, insights and opportunities for companies to make use of AI But if you can’t wait, we’re open for If you’d like to get in early and chat about working together, please email us at e , or buzz me, Nick Nettleton, at the Loft Group office, +44 Meanwhile, you can lean more about Loft here . One final quote from the Deep Learning Summit : “With the exponential growth of deep learning research in recent years, innovative new companies are often funded, acquired and transformed from startups to industry leaders extremely ” Credits: Omnibot photo CC , by Jennifer , via Wikipedia . Email us at Stop Chasing Paper Start Closing COMPANY About Us Pricing Press RESOURCES Blog FAQs FOR YOU Real Estate Brokerages Title Companies LEGAL Terms of Use Privacy Policy Security CONNECT WITH US LinkedIn All rights   About Us - Login Login About Us Pricing FAQs Contact Us About Us Pricing FAQs Contact Us Our Story If anyone knows the pain caused by chasing paper checks, it’s us! As operators of a title insurance agency, we’ve been dealing with issues like bounced checks, incorrect wiring instructions or delayed closings because a client is waiting in line at the bank for a certified check, for over a decade! While growing our title agency from a small regional company into a national presence, we saw new technologies emerge to help with the loan origination, loan processing, client notifications, but the last piece of the puzzle – the cash to close – was still not digital and very We’ve built to help eliminate the inefficiencies of chasing paper checks and the stress caused by wire Our proprietary ACH solution helps prospective home buyers deposit their earnest money, directly from their checking account, when making an offer on a It also helps clients who are refinancing, transfer the funds needed for their cash to close to the title company’s escrow is the quick, digital, secure, and simple way to send money during any real estate As more clients began to use our platform and started gaining interest from real estate agents and other title companies we soon realized our homegrown solution could help an entire industry and decided to share it with the world! FAQ - SchoolHouse How It Works FAQs Meet Our Teachers Become a Teacher Learn More How it Works FAQs Meet our Teachers Become a Teacher Learn More Frequently asked questions Contact us at or browse the topics below to find what you re looking About General questions Getting started Legal Health & safety Curriculum Why microschools? The microschool is the reinvention of the schoolhouse, with small class sizes of students and level Microschools allow parents to choose the best education for their child s needs and creates a small ratio so that each student gets individualized attention from the What is SchoolHouse? SchoolHouse takes the work out of providing your child with the best We enable parents to partner up with families in their community to form a microschool with a group of kids and match you with the best and brightest educator in your Once a match has been made we can register your microschool with your state to ensure compliance and we can even provide a written transcript for your Why should I choose SchoolHouse? SchoolHouse brings the best parts of education to your home with excellent teachers, small class sizes, and a personalized We provide all the tools you need to ensure that your child(ren) receive an enriching, educational experience, with greater flexibility and more personalized attention than traditional schools can offer - all in a safe and inspiring home learning This isn t just about COVID replacement, we are focusing on building a better way to Why does the teacher matter so much? Think back to the best education experiences you ve had, chances are you re thinking of a Research supports that teachers have the largest impact on student satisfaction and educational SchoolHouse enables parents to choose the teacher that is right for them . What is a pod? A pod is a group of approximately students, of roughly the same grade level, who are learning, socializing, and growing We pair a teacher with the pod and then you have your own Our pods run for hours a day, 5 days a During that time, students learn reading, writing, math, history, science, and more! Who are the teachers? We hire only the best teachers using a rigorous screening For every 1 teacher that we hire, we interview approximately Our teachers have on average years of teaching experience, often have advanced degrees, and come highly recommended by What is your screening and vetting process? We screen and vet every We recruit teachers from a variety of backgrounds including private, public, and charter We hire only a small percentage of the teachers we interview and offer competitive packages and small class sizes to attract top Are all teachers certified? We instead focus on recruiting great teachers with several years of teaching experience who are passionate about their subject What grades does SchoolHouse provide services for? We currently provide services for students in grades Do students need to be the same age? We offer pods so every student doesn t need to be the same age or in the same Since there are just a few students in each pod, the teacher will be able to dedicate individual attention to each For many group based activities, students of different ages or grade levels can all Other times, the teacher will differentiate the learning Is there a minimum commitment length? Yes, the minimum commitment is for one Do you offer and options? We offer two standard versions of the program: Replacement and School Replacement is hours per week (5 hours per day, 5 days a week) and the School Enrichment program is hours per week (5 hours per day, 2 days per week). How much does it cost? The cost varies depending on your location, the amount of students in the pod, and the amount of experience the teacher We believe in paying teachers a livable wage and that includes a generous salary, plus Sample price calculator Who handles the administrative work? SchoolHouse does! We take care of the insurance, legal support, academic and curriculum support, contracts, and We take care of all of these issues so that you and the teacher can focus on providing the best educational experience Is SchoolHouse available in my area? We are currently operating and providing full services in the following areas: Illinois, Texas, New York, New Jersey, California, Massachusetts, Florida, Connecticut, Maryland, Virginia, and Washington In these states we can match you with a pod, match you with a teacher, and take care of all of the administrative For all other areas in the United States , we can provide administrative services (insurance, legal support, academic & curriculum support, contracts, and enrollment) if you already have a pod and a Can SchoolHouse help me form my pod? We have a Facebook group where parents are trying to meet each other, share tips, and start their pods We know how hard forming a pod can be and we are developing tools to help you find other families - more on that to come very soon! Where do we host the learning pod? Learning

extracellular proteins Targeted protein degradation has emerged as a powerful new drug modality with applications in a broad range of To date, protein degradation efforts have been applied successfully to intracellular protein Avilar is now expanding the reach and therapeutic potential of protein degradation to the broad universe of extracellular ATACs are a new class of degraders for targeting extracellular proteins The asialoglycoprotein receptor (ASGPR) is an endocytotic cell surface receptor that plays a key role in a natural process through endogenous proteins are internalized into hepatocytes and ATACs (ASGPR Targeting Chimeras) are designed to harness this natural ASGPR degradation ATACs are molecules comprising a ligand that binds to ASGPR, conjugated to a second ligand that binds to a extracellular ATACs work by binding to and shuttling proteins from circulation to the hepatocyte endolysosome, where the unwanted proteins are Our drug discovery platform enables the modular design and assembly of ATACs to target diverse proteins We have built a modular and scalable drug discovery platform for the design and assembly of ATACs that target a wide array of extracellular Key components of the Avilar drug discovery platform include: Novel ASGPR Chemistries Using an structure guided approach, we discovered a library of small molecule, high affinity ASGPR ligands that offer monovalent functionality and superior properties versus historical ASGPR binders Modular Assembly Our optimized small molecule ASGPR ligands are modular and can be efficiently incorporated into ATACs with different protein binders to target a wide range of extracellular proteins Extracellular Degradation Modeling We developed specialized mathematical modeling tools to integrate and predict the unique biophysical, pharmacokinetic, and pharmacodynamic characteristics of endocytosis and degradation Proteome Mapping Proteome mapping is our protein informatics system that extensively catalogues extracellular protein information and enables advanced insights for pipeline target selection, protein binder design, and ATAC development Using our discovery platform, Maybe you have some Bitcoin in cold storage or on Coinbase and you’re curious what this DeFi thing is all about… You re in the right place! This page has everything you need to get started earning DeFi yields on your Bitcoin with It assumes you ve never interacted with the world of decentralized finance Badger Bitcoin is a digital asset stored on the Bitcoin blockchain . BadgerDAO is a decentralized finance (DeFi) application built on Ethereum smart Until recently, the Bitcoin and Ethereum blockchains operated This meant that (despite holding a revolutionary, asset) Bitcoin users were shut out from the main benefits that DeFi has to offer, which are: Earning yield, usually much higher than those available in traditional finance while Maintaining control of your private keys so you stay fully in charge of your assets Where do these amazing yields in DeFi come from? There are three main areas: Yield Farming: New DeFi startups are constantly Many of them provide tokens as a reward for depositing assets into their protocols, known as "yield " Lending: Like traditional finance, you can earn interest by supplying assets to be These loans are typically secured by an amount larger than the loan and will be automatically paid back if the collateral value drops, making them extremely safe for the Providing Liquidity: You can supply assets to markets that let users swap between In exchange, users receive a portion of the trading The landscape of these opportunities is constantly changing – and this is where BadgerDAO comes Think of BadgerDAO like a crypto asset We provide tools that allow you to bring your Bitcoin into DeFi and earn the best yield possible, automatically rebalancing into better strategies as they become With BadgerDAO, you can rest easy knowing you never have to give up the private keys for your crypto, you can withdraw anytime you like, and our strategists are working day and night to put your assets to Before You Start Before starting with BadgerDAO, you need to get setup to interact with both the Bitcoin and Ethereum If your assets are on a custodial exchange like Coinbase or Binance, you will need to move them off exchange and into your private wallet before you interact with BadgerDAO or any other DeFi This is because BadgerDAO is , meaning you maintain full control over your private keys at all times, and decentralized, meaning that our protocol is secured by the network of over ,000 Ethereum nodes located all around the world, rather than a single point of your crypto can be daunting, but please take your time to familiarize yourself with how to send transactions and secure your private If you have any questions, you can always ask in our Discord here (it is monitored 7 by support team members). You will need: A Bitcoin wallet and some Bitcoin (the assets you plan to deposit in BadgerDAO) An Ethereum wallet and some ETH (to pay transaction fees on Ethereum) A hardware wallet such as a Ledger or Trezor (strongly recommended for security) A Web3 browser extension like MetaMask (connects the Badger app to the Ethereum blockchain and lets you approve transactions) A basic understanding of crypto security best practices Bridge Your BTC into Badger Sett Vaults offers over a dozen automated strategies to earn yield on assets, for example wrapped Bitcoin (wBTC) or Badger s own Interest Bearing Bitcoin (ibBTC) . Normally, depositing into these requires several different The good news is, by using Badger Bridge , you can "zap" from BTC directly into four of our top performing Vaults using a single Once your assets are in a Vault, they start earning Some of the rewards are back into your balance, while others need to be claimed via another With BadgerDAO, there is no lockup period which means you can withdraw your assets at any Below, we re going to walk you through how to go from Bitcoin into our bCRVrenBTC vault, which is currently yielding % APY, but can be boosted to over % (see "Boost" below for details). Ready? Let s go: Step 1: Visit https: app.badger.com bridge Step 2: Connect MetaMask Step 3: Click "Mint & Earn" and input the amount of BTC you would like to Select the "bCRVrenBTC" vault from the dropdown menu and click "Next." Keep in mind: The minimum is The Ethereum and Bitcoin networks charge fees for These rise and fall based on market conditions, but $100-150 is a normal These fees may not make it economical to deposit small Step 4: Confirm Fees You will see a confirmation page that estimates all the fees associated with the Keep in mind that Ethereum fees vary due to network If the fees are higher than expected, you can try at a different time (weekends are usually lower) After reviewing the information, click "Confirm" to Step 5: Deposit your BTC to the Bridge Send funds from

Cannabis - Zip Run Zip Run Zip Run Sign Up Sign In Cannabis Everything you need to know about Cannabis! Common Terms , Plant Basics , Ways to Consume Welcome! If you’re trying cannabis for the first time or trying again after a long time, our goal is to make sure you have all the information you need to make a We’ve curated some of the most commonly used words and phrases, tips for consumption, and we’re outlining the differences between Sativa, Indica, and Hybrids, and so much Plus, the Zip Run team is always ready to help you out with any This is all new to me where do I start? No worries, We’ve got Cannabis There are many ways to enjoy the benefits of While most people are familiar with smoking, there are many other avenues to Delicious edibles that you eat, topicals that you place on your skin, vapes that allow you to smoke concentrated cannabis oil, sublinguals, which are cannabis oil suspensions, or dabs which are very heavily concentrated amounts of cannabis extract that are heated at a very high temperature and No matter which of these methods you choose, make sure you start with a tiny dose and work your way up from Remember that cannabis affects each person differently, and some new users may not feel the full effect, or any at all, the first time they try Um, it’s been a while since I rolled my own or hit a What’s the latest and greatest? Get excited — this is not the marijuana you grew up with or smoked at college! The legal market today is packed full of amazing new products and new ways to But, heads up, it can be a lot more potent than you remember, so slow your roll and see how you feel before gobbling up a handful of Times have changed, and you’re probably going to need to learn a few new names and terms — check out the glossary below provided by Leafly for more detailed What’s the deal with Sativa, Indica, and Hybrids? Sativa is more likely to provide more uplifting and cerebral effects that pair well with creative, social, and physical Indica has a calming and relaxing More potent varieties numb your body and put you to It’s great for stress relief and perfect for a long Saturday afternoon when all you want is Netflix and your Hybrid strains bring together the best of both worlds! A great Hybrid will be uplifting, mellow, creative, and Ultimately, it boils down to personal Hybrids can be Sativa or Indica dominant and have the effects to Common Terms Adult Use “Adult-use” and “recreational” mean the same thing: Cannabis that can be bought by adults + in a legal the only difference is that some state legislatures use one term over the other in their There is no difference between cannabis products labeled with either of these Budtender An employee at a cannabis store who is responsible for helping Job duties include educating the public on cannabis products and helping customers navigate and purchase cannabis Budtenders use their expertise in cannabis to help guide people through the cannabis Dispensary Dispensaries are licensees in the cannabis industry who dispense products to patients and Some states permit dispensaries to deliver cannabis products directly to customers at their homes in addition to dispensing them at a Eighth An eighth (⅛) is a measurement of cannabis It is the shorthand for “one-eighth of an ounce,” or Cannabis shops and dispensaries sell cannabis in a variety of different weights, the most common of which are grams, eighths, quarters, , and Depending on how big the bowl is on your pipe or bong, an eighth of cannabis will typically provide you with seven to ten Endocannabinoid System The endocannabinoid system is a system of receptors throughout the brain and body that respond to compounds in cannabis like THC, resulting in a range of different subjective and therapeutic Our bodies naturally produce molecules called endocannabinoids which bind to these receptors, though cannabis also interacts with Researchers believe the endocannabinoid system’s primary function is to maintain balanced functioning in our bodies and to regulate signaling in the Entourage Effect The phenomenon that all compounds in the cannabis plant, including cannabinoids, terpenes, and more, work together synergistically to provide greater effects and health benefits than by themselves when consumed—the sum is greater than the whole of the Because of this, many cannabis consumers subscribe to whole plant medicine, as opposed to consuming isolated cannabinoids or other Strain A strain refers to the named variations of cannabis that differ in appearance, aroma, and Cannabis grows natively in different regions of the world and has been selectively bred for various Terms like “sativa” and “indica” describe different structural differences in the plant: narrow broad leaves, tall short stature, Cannabis strains that has been crossbred are called hybrids, which make up a vast majority of cannabis available Terpenes Terpenes are the aromatic compounds that give cannabis strains their unique In other words,

For more details on cookies please visit All About Cookies . ​ [ Analytics : We use Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google, (“Google”).
